# RULES.md is mandatory (not optional memory)

**Source of truth:** [`notes/guide3/RULES.md`](../../notes/guide3/RULES.md) (read with the Read tool — never rely on conversation memory).

## When to read (every time, not once per session)

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| Session start / user assigns implementation | Read RULES.md (full file or Tripwires + Section 3 + 5 + 7 + 9) |
| Before **any** code edit | Re-read Section 3, 7, Tripwire 8 (trace full pipeline) |
| Before **any** fix/architecture suggestion | Re-read Section 5 + 12; reject if it matches a failure pattern |
| Before **any** test run | Re-read Section 9 |

If you cannot confirm compliance, stop and read RULES.md before proceeding.

## Non-negotiable constraints (violations = rejected work)

- **No band-aids:** no repetition detectors, auto-cancel, post-hoc stripping, retries/limiters that fix symptoms after the fact
- **No per-model hacks:** arch-family profiles only (`generationProfiles.js` / `modelProfiles.js`), no `if (qwen35)` branches
- **Root cause at source:** correct sampler/config/pipeline phase — not detectors
- **No guessing:** research or read code; definitive answers only
- **Production quality:** simple correct fix beats layered systems; over-engineering also banned
- **Trace full pipeline** before changing one file (Tripwire 8)

## Suggestions and plans must be checked

Before presenting a plan or code change to the user, explicitly verify it does **not** violate Section 5 (Failure Patterns) or Section 12 (Past Failures). If it resembles a past failure, do not suggest it unless you document why it is different.

## Cursor rules stack

This file works with `plan-execute-ship.mdc`: implementing a plan still requires obeying RULES.md **and** shipping (push, tag, CI green) as the final step.
